Class Book

  • java.lang.Object
    • Book
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Book>
    public class Book
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Book>
    The Book class contains fields/methods for an object of type Book. Each Book has an automatically-generated 5-digit serial number. Methods included to compare Books, as well as return a String literal describing their data field contents.
    Author:
    Michael Choe, Sagnik Mukherjee

      • tryCheckOut

        public boolean tryCheckOut()
        Attempts to check out this Book object. If the book is already checked out, tryCheckOut() fails and we cannot check out the book. If it is available, the book is now checked out, and tryCheckOut() succeeds.
        Returns:
        false if this.checkedOut is initially true, true otherwise

      • tryReturns

        public boolean tryReturns()
        Attempts to return this Book object. If the book is already available, tryReturns() fails and we cannot return the book. If it is checked out, the book is now returned, and tryReturns() succeeds.
        Returns:
        false if this.checkedOut is initially false, true otherwise
